name: Christina Hill
text: Nice quaint take out pizzeria.

name: bow one
text: Order was processed later than the stated on-line time. And the pizza seemed light on toppings. I'm a regular customer and today's experience was average at best. Customer service face-time was great as usual, friendly staff.

name: Alex Harris
text: More of a 3.5, I've been a very regular customer at this location. Few things to keep it from a 5. I've been called twice later at night saying they were closing, it was 12:30 and online and store says 3am. Okay. I tried ordering online â€¦More

name: David Chambers
text: Pizza is hit or miss. I have had several pizzas where the crust accounts for way too much of the pizza; the toppings and cheese stopped several inches from the edge. When it's good, it's pretty decent, but there isn't enough consistency to continue to order from here.

name: Amanda Rosemark
text: We've been ordering from this location for years, but it's been on the steady decline. There is little consistency to the quality and sadly as of late is usually not good. A few months ago we got food poisoning from their chicken wings and â€¦More

name: Greg Rowland
text: Offers a somewhat different take on the typical Pizza Place.  In addition to Toppers sticks (which I believe are the best item on the menu), they have some non traditional pizza options such as Mac and Cheese, Taco topper, and one with Tater Tots.

name: Jenne Siltberg
text: Came an hour after ordering instead of 40 minutes. Forgot receipt to tip. Slower delivery and smaller portions vs sarpinos or Domino's. I work late shift and want to go to bed. My food arrived room temperature! I put it in fridge, good night ðŸ˜©

name: Angusari Kempachi
text: Some of the best pizza I've had. Their prices are comparable if not better than a few of the other local pizza places and have better quality pizza. I got to try the topperstix and I will be getting those from now on. The store seems a â€¦More

name: Alex Burton
text: Service was fine, but when i got home i opened the pizza to find half of the toppings are missing. When you order a specialty pizza it ends up pretty dissapointing for flavor without half the ingredients. Overall fail.

name: Marcelo DaSilveira
text: Stupid web site. Wasted a bunch of time trying to order my pizza only to keep getting an error, so much for the only online special. Called the store but nobody cares. I just gave up from frustration and ordered from a competitor. Never had â€¦More

name: Chuck Zandy
text: I ordered a 2-topping large pizza for carry-out. Their Web site charged me $9.99. I noticed a sign when I picked up saying $7.99 for a large 2-topping pizza for carry-out, but it didn't really register until after I left, so I called them â€¦More

name: Greg Lobeck
text: I really liked their chicken wings. I had the oven roasted style. They were very moist, cooked very well, and had generous potions of meat on each one. â€¦More

name: mark bedney
text: ok pizza nothing really special topper stix were tasty

name: Craig Nilles
text: Easy online ordering and quick pickup.  Pizza is good too.

name: Kyle Waid
text: I ordered pizza late at night. The delivery driver did not come to the correct street. I had my phone on mute so I did not know they had called me but was looking out the window and they never arrived. I finally saw 45 minutes later that â€¦More

name: rylan kinnell
text: I ordered on a Sunday right before 3am. They were polite and courteous over the phone and delivered it in less than 30 minutes. Food was amazing. This is my new go to for pizza delivery. They are awesome.

name: Chaz Christensen
text: Great Place! The ingredients are good, service is good, and love all the options for toppings and sauces! Wings are great too! We loved it and highly recommend it!

name: Johnny Bauer
text: I'm a truck driver and although I'm local I often have to stay in my truck throughout the week which leaves me very limited to  where I can choose. I have ordered from this location several times because it shows up hot and fresh most â€¦More

name: justin johnson
text: Ordered pizzas with extra sauce and received extra no-sauce. They came out more like giant breadsticks. I contacted Toppers twice about the disappointment and received no response. Would have expected better.

name: Anna Adelmann
text: Ordered online. Delivery time 9:15pm itâ€™s now 10pm and itâ€™s still not here. We called and they said it was on itâ€™s way that was 20 minutes ago! NEVER ordering here again! Terrible customer service

name: Jasmine Lazo
text: Best pizza I've gotten so far ! Toppers rocks plus this store is amazing great management and great workers keep up the good work ! Best crust I ever tasted

name: Ben Frisvold
text: Jordan, the manager, would rather argue than fulfill simple customer requests.

name: Craig Smith
text: Great quality food, great service

name: Sophie
text: I love the bread sticks here. The pizza is amazing, but the bread stocks steal the spotlight. I would highly recommend this pizza place to anyone that likes pizza or good bread sticks.

name: Peter Anderson
text: The topperstix are so delicious they should be illegal.  We skip the pizza and go for the stix.

name: Sonny Morning
text: Love their pizza!!! 2nd best in town!!!

name: Hollis Joslin
text: These guys are great. I have ordered from them a few times and they always deliver quickly. On top of this, the food is great. Try out the TopperStix!

name: Bennett Olson
text: Gotta love some toppers. Wish they had a bigger delivery zone. :(

name: Michelle Theis

name: justin toll
text: They cant even get an order over the phone correct let alone offer any deal/specials..... $26 one topping pizza and wings lol what a joke save your money its not even that good

name: michelle pahl

name: jack pool
text: Gave me two "medium" pizzas. One pizza was a medium and the other was a small. I called them and confronted them about it, they denied it being small. Smh go somewhere else!

text: I called and tried to make a order, and some lady that work there was so rude , it sounded like she hated her job. She told me it would take 2 hours to delievery a medium chicken pizza. I told her I was going to recall because it sounded â€¦More

name: Jane Jane
text: Ordered a pizza, never showed up, called back over an hour later and was told that it was on its way, called back 20 minutes after that and was treated like I was annoying the person on the phone, asked if there was a manager to speak to â€¦More

name: Melanie Savage
text: Placed an order over the phone and was very clear I wanted a buffalo chicken pizza but with no buffalo sauce, also asked if they sold 2 liter bottles of pop he said yes so I ordered that too. Total came out to $22. When I get there to pick â€¦More

text: Our go to for pizza, fast delivery, always fresh

name: Booust Kunst
text: why did they close? my favorite pizza.

text: I have ordered from here 2ce and the first time received cold, cardboard-like pizza over 2 hours after I ordered and the second time with my pizza never coming at all. Not ordering from here again.

text: pizza how it's wanted and you can make it how you want it. No Wait, friendly people and they deliver.

text: Pizza and wings were mediocre and cold by the time they got here. Won't order again there is better options in Eagan.

text: Toppers had a two or more items for 5.99 advertised.  I ordered five items and they said I couldn't have the 5.99 deal on all of them.  The ad did not say anything about a limit.   One of the two pizzas I ordered was cold and I picked my order up when they said it would be ready.

name: Blurtis
text: Worst thin crust pizza in town. Go to Cub, buy a Jack's pizza and pop it in the oven for 5 minutes at 350 and you'll have a $15 Toppers pizza!
